HEADWORD: Exodic
<hw>Ex*od"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ belonging to
departure. See <er>Exodus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Conducting influences from the spinal cord outward; -- said of the
motor or efferent nerves. Opposed to <contr>esodic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>exodontics</ent>⟦br⟧
